1. *Vuk* je opasan predator. (The *wolf* is a dangerous predator.)
2. Čuli smo *vukove* kako zavijaju u daljini. (We heard *wolves* howling in the distance.)
3. Lovci su upućeni na tragove *vuka*. (Hunters are following the tracks of a *wolf*.)
4. *Vukovi* su se okupili u čoporu. (The *wolves* have gathered in a pack.)
5. U pričama iz naše narodne tradicije, *vuk* obično predstavlja zlo. (In the stories from our folk tradition, *the wolf* usually represents evil.)
6. Planina *Vuk* je dom za mnoge divlje životinje. (The mountain *Vuk* is home to many wild animals.)
7. Ova pesma govori o ljubavi između *vuka* i devojke. (This song is about the love between a *wolf* and a girl.)
8. Polarni *vuk* ima debelu belu dlaku koja mu pomaže da se zagreje. (The Arctic *wolf* has thick white fur that helps it stay warm.)
9. *Vuk* je spreman da se bori za svoj teritorij. (The *wolf* is ready to fight for its territory.)
10. *Vuk* je bio jedan od najvažnijih mitoloških likova u slavenskoj kulturi. (The *wolf* was one of the most important mythological figures in Slavic culture.)